## Wiring Overview

- Feather ESP32 V2 to GPS: UART TX/RX  
- OLED via SPI (SCK, MOSI, DC, CS, RST)  
- SD via SPI (shared bus with OLED, separate CS)  
- Buttons to GPIOs with pull-up resistors  
- Battery plugs into Feather JST connector (auto-charging)  
- Switch optionally connected to Feather EN for hard power cutoff

---

## Powering On / Charging

1. Plug in USB-C to charge the battery and/or upload firmware
2. Disconnect USB to run fully on battery
3. Toggle switch to power on/off (optional but recommended)

---

## Optional Upgrades

- Add BLE lap beacon triggers using Feather BLE capabilities
- Add G-sensor via I2C or analog input
- Add NeoPixel strip or ring for lap/impact indication

